text: Yes, that would indeed be an NX class ship. One thing to remember about the JJverse, Star Trek: Enterprise happened "exactly" as it did for the prime universe. It only split off afterwards for the beginning of Kirks time. So all the adventures of Captain Archer and the events of the early Starfleet (with the help of Vulcan) has happened. It would only make sense for NX class ships to still be used in some fashion in this timeline. Many thanks to Justin Lin for including actual Star Trek lore.

text: Yeah, the trailer is better than the first one, but it still doesn't feel like ST to me. It's probably going to have just as much a lack of great character interaction, human(ist) values and ideas, and an overabundance of action as Into Darkness. Not to mention there's probably no ''trekking'' anywhere. Looks like they're also going to cram Kirk's backstory or character info into one movie... great. Before this trailer, many people thought it looked terrible, but now it's the best thing ever? Please.  A few nice-"looking" scenes won't make it better. I think people were so disappointed by other movie trailers (Ghostbusters, for instance) they're now giving this one too much credit.

text: I'll be honest.. This looks pretty impressive , and I'll admit the teaser with the Beastie Boys song sabotage did feel out of place.. But then I looked at it from a different prospective , it's that the teaser had a lot of fast pace action and being Hollywood they went with a pretty generic song that they hoped would pleas fans and non fans of Star Trek .. Some liked it while die hard fans thought it was incoherent ... Now I am going to come out and say that I am not a huge Star Trek fan and yes I do prefer the Star Wars films , But what JJ Abrams did when he was asked to do a reboot of the series he made it appeal and loved by not just fans and non fans but also movie goers who love thrilling stories of Adventure and or character development ... I admire what Star Trek is and won't dislike people who love it , My only hope is like with the first two films it will surprise us with new elements withing the original universe but be like it's own thing with these characters story arcs in the alternate time line ... V *Live long , and prosper*

text: I think that is the NX-01 enterprise at 2:06 . Beyond just looking like it, we see kirk at 2:11 wearing a uniform jacket that is similar to the style worn by Archer in his time, stark Navy Blue with 4 yellow shoulder lines. Then if you look at 2:12 you can see the bridge is very old and outdated, with computer screens displaying greenline readouts, compared to the Apple store look that all the trek ships have in this cannon, plus you look at the ceiling lights and their covered in dust and dirt, suggesting the ships been sitting a very long time. And in one of the prior trailers you see scotty walk onto a bridge thats rusted, and beat up. I dont believe this is a modern ship successor to the NX class as it wouldnt be this woefully outdated. It would be awesome in a way to see the very first enterprise reactivated to go to battle one final time under the command of Kirk. And make JJ abrahms total molestation of the entire trek cannon complete!

text: The problem with this Capt Kirk is that they're attempting to make him moody, contemplative, and unsure of himself. A beta male. What made the original Capt Kirk so successful was that he was the exact opposite: confident, secure in his beliefs to the point of reckless, but knowing he'd find a way out. An Alpha male. On a characterization scale, the former, you can empathize with; the latter, you wish you were like. The latter is thus more heroic.

text: Hello Everyone, I feel I need to post this. For those who might have missed it, due to a fan based film both CBS and Paramount have issued "guidelines" that actually destroy all the possibilities of anymore real fan based trek films in the future. If you would like to know more search for "star trek prelude to Axanar" and watch the previews and details about the show. There are many fan based films for you to watch and some are really good considering they are not made by a real studio. You will even see a few real actors are involved and the efforts have been made to have a very high quality of production. Yes, some not so much but its about Star Trek not production. Now please consider that for many years now they (CBS and Paramount) have allowed a few groups to make many really good (and some not so good) episodes based on Star Trek in many versions as long as they do not "make a profit" from the production. To actual start making the episode Axanar they had a fund drive and made over 1 million US Dollars so, CBS and Paramount sued them to stop production. Recently they released the "guidelines" for all future fan based films that are not only not constitutional points (like actors who worked in any trek can’t work in fan based films and vice a versa) but limit production time and costs in such a way that means no less than a clear effort to kill all fan based Star Trek films. Read the complete set of guidelines here: http://www.startrek.com/fan-films I ask all fans to get educated on these Star Trek fan based films to read up on this matter. Please learn the facts about the past films and the possibility of future for more of them. If you cannot agree that CBS and Paramount be allowed to force these guidelines on fan film production please help us stop them. Also please compare the way the fan films for Star Wars are treated where they even offer a public awards show for them. I, and other Star Trek fans are calling for a boycott of the upcoming movie and the 2017 series on CBS unless they publicly stop this and provide the fans with a reasonable and legal ability to enjoy others ideas of the Star Trek world. They have allowed it for years but now they are moving to kill them while hoping it won’t affect them making more money off Star Trek. So, let’s boycott them and stop the money they would make from the 7-22 release of Star Trek Beyond and the 2017 series planned to have one show on TV then the rest on a pay service only from CBS. If they see enough decrease of the upcoming movie sales they will obey us as the fans and workout a real reasonable way for them to continue without the idiotic and illegal current guidelines. I, and more than 20 people I know have agreed to boycott the new film unless this is fixed right.  Thanks for your time.
